FileQuery is an innovative project designed to revolutionize document-based question answering. By leveraging the power of machine learning and natural language processing, FileQuery enables users to extract valuable insights and answers from PDF, PPT, or DOCX files with ease.

Features:

Document Training: Users can upload their PDF, PPT, or DOCX files to train the model.
Advanced Techniques: FileQuery utilizes cutting-edge technologies such as LangChain, GenAI, and FAISS for efficient model training and document analysis.
Interactive Interface: With the help of Streamlit, FileQuery offers an intuitive and user-friendly interface. Users can seamlessly ask questions related to the uploaded document and receive accurate answers in real-time.
Versatile Application: Whether it's extracting key information from research papers, presentations, or reports, FileQuery empowers users to navigate through vast amounts of textual data effortlessly.
Scalability: The project is designed to handle large volumes of documents, making it suitable for a wide range of applications across industries.
Usage:

Clone Repository: Clone the FileQuery repository to your local machine.
Install Dependencies: Install the required dependencies listed in the requirements.txt file using pip install -r requirements.txt.
Run Application: Execute the Streamlit application by running the command streamlit run app.py in your terminal.
Upload Documents: Upload PDF, PPT, or DOCX files to train the model and start asking questions.
Ask Questions: Utilize the interactive interface to ask questions related to the document content and receive accurate responses in real-time.
